{"id":113273,"date":"2025-02-19T05:30:45","date_gmt":"2025-02-18T19:30:45","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/?p=113273"},"modified":"2025-02-19T13:41:11","modified_gmt":"2025-02-19T03:41:11","slug":"navigating-dual-anzsco-catalogues-on-anzscosearch","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/navigating-dual-anzsco-catalogues-on-anzscosearch\/","title":{"rendered":"Navigating Dual ANZSCO Catalogues On Anzscosearch"},"content":{"rendered":"[vc_row type=&#8221;in_container&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; scene_position=&#8221;center&#8221; text_color=&#8221;dark&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; row_border_radius_applies=&#8221;bg&#8221; overflow=&#8221;visible&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; shape_divider_position=&#8221;bottom&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221;][vc_column column_padding=&#8221;no-extra-padding&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_direction_desktop=&#8221;default&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; desktop_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; tablet_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; phone_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_backdrop_filter=&#8221;none&#8221; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; column_position=&#8221;default&#8221; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;1\/1&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; animation_type=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_style=&#8221;solid&#8221;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]As of <strong>7 December 2024<\/strong>, the Department of Home Affairs has introduced significant legislative changes that affect how occupations are classified for various Australian visas. At Anzscosearch, we are committed to guiding you through these updates, though the task is complex.[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]\n<h2><strong>Dual-Catalogue System<\/strong><\/h2>\n[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]The changes to employer-sponsored visas (Subclass 482 and 186) have introduced an updated ANZSCO catalogue (<strong>ANZSCO v2022<\/strong>), which reflects the Australian and New Zealand Standard Classification of Occupations as in force on <strong>23 November 2022<\/strong>. However, many other visas still rely on the older <strong>ANZSCO v1.2<\/strong> (in force on 27 June 2013).<\/p>\n<p>This dual-catalogue system creates complexities. The new ANZSCO v2022 not only amends occupation descriptions and tasks but also <u>changes occupation codes<\/u> or <u>names<\/u> and even <u>removes certain occupations<\/u> in some cases. For example, \u201cCabinetmaker\u201d now appears under two distinct codes and with a slightly updated name:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Cabinetmaker ANZSCO 39411<strong>1<\/strong> \u2013 Listed under ANZSCO v1.2 (older version)<\/li>\n<li>Cabinet Maker ANZSCO 39411<strong>2<\/strong> \u2013 Listed under ANZSCO v2022 (newer version)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]\n<h2><strong>Which Visas Use Which Catalogue?<\/strong><\/h2>\n[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]The following table provides an overview of each visa subclass and corresponding stream, including the applicable occupation lists and the relevant ANZSCO catalogue.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-113338\" src=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/anzsco-catalogues.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1096\" height=\"879\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/anzsco-catalogues.png 1096w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/anzsco-catalogues-300x241.png 300w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/anzsco-catalogues-1024x821.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/anzsco-catalogues-768x616.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1096px) 100vw, 1096px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]In summary:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>ANZSCO <strong>v1.2<\/strong> is relevant to Subclass 189, 190, 491, 485, 494, 407, and 187 visas.<\/li>\n<li>ANZSCO <strong>v2022 <\/strong>is relevant to Subclass 482 (Core &amp; Specialist streams) and 186 (TRT &amp; DE).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>A <strong>mix of both catalogues<\/strong>, as well as <strong>non-ANZSCO occupations<\/strong> with a 6-digit code of 070499, is used under the Labour Agreement stream of Subclass 482, 186 and 494.<\/p>\n<p>Source: <a class=\"uline\" href=\"https:\/\/www.legislation.gov.au\/F2024L01616\/asmade\/text\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Migration (ANZSCO Definition) Specification 2024<\/a> <i class=\"icon-tiny fa fa-external-link\"><\/i>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]\n<h2><strong>What are the Challenges?<\/strong><\/h2>\n[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]Using multiple catalogues introduces the following issues:<\/p>\n<h3>1. Occupations in the v1.2 catalogue which do not exist in the new v2022 catalogue because they are obsolete or have been <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">replaced<\/span> by a new occupation.<\/h3>\n<p>Case in Point:<\/p>\n<pre>262112 ICT Security Specialist<\/pre>\n<p>This occupation is in the v1.2 catalogue and is included in the MLTSSL list. It is eligible for Subclasses 189, 190, 491, 485, 494, and 407.<\/p>\n<p>However, this occupation does NOT exist in the new v2022 catalogue; therefore, it is no longer eligible for Subclass 482 and 186. This occupation has been replaced by:<\/p>\n<pre>262116 Cyber Security Analyst<\/pre>\n<p>The Cyber Security Analyst is in the v2022 catalogue. It is a new occupation included in the CSOL list and is eligible for Subclasses 482 and 186.<\/p>\n<h3>2. Occupations in the v1.2 catalogue that exist in the new v2022 catalogue but with a different or <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">updated code<\/span>.<\/h3>\n<p>Case in Point:<\/p>\n<pre>362212 Arborist (v1.2) vs 362511 Arborist (v2022)<\/pre>\n<h3>3. Occupations listed in the v1.2 catalogue that exist in the new v2022 catalogue but with a different or <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">updated name<\/span>.<\/h3>\n<p>Case in Point:<\/p>\n<pre>322211 Sheetmetal Trades Worker vs 322211 Sheetmetal Worker<\/pre>\n<h3>4. Occupations in the v1.2 catalogue that exist in the new v2022 catalogue but with a different or <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">updated code and name<\/span>.<\/h3>\n<p>Case in Point:<\/p>\n<pre>394111 Cabinetmaker (v1.2) vs 394112 Cabinet Maker (v2022)<\/pre>\n<h3>5. New occupations included in the v2022 catalogue that did not exist in the v1.2 catalogue.<\/h3>\n<p>Case in Point:<\/p>\n<pre>139917 Regulatory Affairs Manager\r\n224114 Data Analysts\r\n224115 Data Scientist<\/pre>\n[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]\n<h2><strong>Anzscosearch\u2019s Approach<\/strong><\/h2>\n[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]To address these challenges, Anzscosearch has taken the following approach:<\/p>\n<h3><strong>1. ANZSCO catalogue v1.2 vs v1.3<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p>In November 2019, the Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS) released a newer version of the v1.2 catalogue, Version 1.3 (v1.3).<\/p>\n<p>This release was limited to updating the indicative skills level for some occupations. It did not result in adding, deleting, or moving any categories within ANZSCO. The changes were kept to a minimum in most cases, limited to removing the words \u201c(Aus) (NZ)\u201d from the title.<\/p>\n<p>Version 1.2 has no longer been maintained by the ABS since 2019.<\/p>\n<p>Anzscosearch is updated to v1.3.<\/p>\n<h3><strong>2. Designated Badge<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p>Each occupation has been assigned an identification \u2018badge\u2019 which labels each occupation as being from the old catalogue (v1.3), the new catalogue (v2022) or both (v1.3 &amp; v2022)<\/p>\n<p>Example of an occupation only in v1.3:<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"94\" class=\"sshadow wp-image-113276 size-large aligncenter\" style=\"width: 700px;\" src=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-1-1024x137.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-1-1024x137.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-1-300x40.png 300w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-1-768x102.png 768w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-1.png 1357w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Example of an occupation only in v2022:<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"92\" class=\"sshadow wp-image-113277 size-large aligncenter\" style=\"width: 700px;\" src=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-2-1024x134.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-2-1024x134.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-2-300x39.png 300w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-2-768x100.png 768w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-2.png 1353w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Example of an occupation in both catalogues with no code or name changes:<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"97\" class=\"sshadow wp-image-113278 size-large aligncenter\" style=\"width: 700px;\" src=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-3-1024x142.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-3-1024x142.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-3-300x42.png 300w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-3-768x106.png 768w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-3.png 1351w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" \/><\/p>\n<h3><strong>3. Search identification<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p>If an occupation exists in both catalogues with <strong>no changes<\/strong> to its code or name, it appears in the search as normal. For example, 234211 Chemist:<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"sshadow size-full wp-image-113279 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-4.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1920\" height=\"786\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-4.png 1920w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-4-300x123.png 300w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-4-1024x419.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-4-768x314.png 768w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-4-1536x629.png 1536w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" \/><br \/>\nIf an occupation exists in both catalogues but its <strong>code or name has changed<\/strong>, it will appear twice in the search\u2014once for each catalogue version (look out for the v2022 badge on the right-hand corner to differentiate between the two occupations). For example, Arborist:<br \/>\n<strong><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"sshadow size-full wp-image-113280 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-5.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1920\" height=\"673\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-5.png 1920w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-5-300x105.png 300w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-5-1024x359.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-5-768x269.png 768w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-5-1536x538.png 1536w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" \/><\/strong><\/p>\n<p>In addition, to highlight these changes, a <strong>red warning icon<\/strong> <i class=\"fa fa-exclamation-triangle\" style=\"font-size: 20px; color: red;\"><\/i> is displayed next to affected occupations.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"123\" class=\"sshadow aligncenter wp-image-114023 size-large\" style=\"width: 700px;\" src=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/warning-indicator-anzsco-1024x180.jpg\" alt=\"dual anzsco occupations\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/warning-indicator-anzsco-1024x180.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/warning-indicator-anzsco-300x53.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/warning-indicator-anzsco-768x135.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/warning-indicator-anzsco.jpg 1435w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Click on the red warning icon to view further details and ensure you select the correct occupation when assessing eligibility.<\/p>\n<p>In regard to eligibility:<\/p>\n<p>\u2705 ANZSCO v1.2 applies to: Subclass 189, 190, 491, 485, 494, 407, and 187 visas.<br \/>\n\u2705 ANZSCO v2022 applies to: Subclass 482 (Core &amp; Specialist streams) and 186 (TRT &amp; DE) visas.<\/p>\n<h3><strong>4. New ANZSCO v2022 Tab<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p>When you select a code from the two catalogues, the search will return two ANZSCO Tabs so that you can navigate the differences in occupation descriptions, tasks, etc.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"172\" class=\"sshadow aligncenter wp-image-113281 size-large\" style=\"width: 700px;\" src=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-6-1024x251.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-6-1024x251.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-6-300x73.png 300w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-6-768x188.png 768w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-6-1536x376.png 1536w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-6.png 1642w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" \/><\/p>\n<h3><strong>5. Information Notes<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p>We have added &#8216;Information Icons&#8217; to display occupation-specific eligibility criteria for the Subclass 482 Specialist Skills stream and the Temporary Residence Transition (TRT) stream of Subclass 186 and 187.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"sshadow size-full wp-image-113282 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-7.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1361\" height=\"625\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-7.png 1361w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-7-300x138.png 300w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-7-1024x470.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/Pic-7-768x353.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1361px) 100vw, 1361px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][divider line_type=&#8221;No Line&#8221; custom_height=&#8221;20&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]\n<h2><strong>OSCA Version 1.0<\/strong><\/h2>\n[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]On 6 December 2024, the <a class=\"uline\" href=\"https:\/\/www.abs.gov.au\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Australian Bureau of Statistics<\/a> <i class=\"icon-tiny fa fa-external-link\"><\/i> (ABS) officially released the <a class=\"uline\" href=\"https:\/\/www.abs.gov.au\/statistics\/classifications\/osca-occupation-standard-classification-australia\/2024-version-1-0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Occupation Standard Classification for Australia<\/a> <i class=\"icon-tiny fa fa-external-link\"><\/i> (OSCA) version 1.0. This new classification replaces the Australian and New Zealand Standard Classification of Occupations (ANZSCO), introducing tailored updates to better reflect Australia\u2019s evolving labour market.<\/p>\n<p>The OSCA version 1.0 catalogue has been added to our website as a separate reference tool. While it provides an updated framework for classifying occupations in line with recent labour market changes, it is important to note that <strong>OSCA v1.0 has not yet been adopted by the Department of Home Affairs for migration and visa purposes<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"191\" class=\"sshadow aligncenter wp-image-113860\" style=\"width: 700px;\" src=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/osca-anzsco.jpg\" alt=\"osca anzsco anzscosearch\" \/><\/p>\n<p>For further details visit: <a class=\"uline\" href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/osca-replaces-anzsco-in-australias-occupational-classification-system\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">OSCA replaces ANZSCO in Australia\u2019s Occupational Classification System<\/a>.[\/vc_column_text][divider line_type=&#8221;Small Line&#8221; line_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; line_thickness=&#8221;1&#8243; divider_color=&#8221;default&#8221; custom_height=&#8221;60&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]\n<h2><strong>Legislation<\/strong><\/h2>\n[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]\n<ul>\n<li><a class=\"uline\" href=\"https:\/\/www.legislation.gov.au\/F2024L01585\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Migration Amendment (2024 Measures No. 1) Regulations 2024<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a class=\"uline\" href=\"https:\/\/www.legislation.gov.au\/F2024L01620\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Migration (Specification of Occupations\u2014Subclass 482 Visa) Instrument 2024<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a class=\"uline\" href=\"https:\/\/www.legislation.gov.au\/F2024L01618\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Migration (Specification of Occupations and Assessing Authorities\u2014Subclass 186 Visa) Instrument 2024<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a class=\"uline\" href=\"https:\/\/www.legislation.gov.au\/F2024L01617\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Migration (Language Test Requirements for Subclass 482 Visa) Instrument 2024<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a class=\"uline\" href=\"https:\/\/www.legislation.gov.au\/F2024L01621\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Migration Amendment (Skills in Demand Visa and Related Matters) Instrument 2024<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a class=\"uline\" href=\"https:\/\/www.legislation.gov.au\/F2024L01619\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Migration (Arrangements for Employer Nomination and Regional Employer Nomination Skilled Visas) Instrument 2024<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a class=\"uline\" href=\"https:\/\/www.legislation.gov.au\/F2024L01615\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Migration Amendment (Skills in Demand and Nil VAC) Instrument 2024<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a class=\"uline\" href=\"https:\/\/www.legislation.gov.au\/F2024L01589\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Migration (Skilling Australians Fund) Charges Amendment (Subclass 482 (Skills in Demand) Visa) Regulations 2024<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a class=\"uline\" href=\"https:\/\/www.legislation.gov.au\/F2024L01616\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Migration (ANZSCO Definition) Specification 2024<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row type=&#8221;in_container&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; scene_position=&#8221;center&#8221; text_color=&#8221;dark&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; row_border_radius_applies=&#8221;bg&#8221; overflow=&#8221;visible&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; shape_divider_position=&#8221;bottom&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221;][vc_column column_padding=&#8221;no-extra-padding&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_direction_desktop=&#8221;default&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; desktop_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; tablet_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; phone_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_backdrop_filter=&#8221;none&#8221; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; column_position=&#8221;default&#8221; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_t